---
description: Scoring behavior and safe language for suspicious activity detection
globs:
  - "apps/api/**/*"
  - "apps/web/**/*"
  - "packages/scoring/**/*"
alwaysApply: true
---

SignalGraph scoring and language policy:

- do not present outputs as proof of fraud
- use language such as:
  - suspicious
  - elevated risk
  - likely inorganic
  - coordinated pattern
  - unexplained burst
  - confidence limited
- every score must be decomposable into features/subscores
- every user-facing score must include explanation text
- score computation should be deterministic where feasible for heuristic MVP logic
- thresholds and weights should be configurable

When creating or editing score logic:
- add raw feature output
- add normalized feature or subscore
- add rationale text
- add tests
- avoid magic numbers without named config

Do not implement a single opaque ML score unless a transparent fallback exists.
